# P2P mesh ‚Äî compact roundtrip

For **Hyperswarm / pairing / Groove mesh UI**, prefer simplification over new layers.

## Canonical data flow

```
Rust: state changed
  ‚Üí GrooveActor: publish_mesh | mesh_refresh_full | peers table snapshot_broadcast
  ‚Üí avenos:runtime { kind: "mesh" | "table" }
  ‚Üí peerMeshSnapshot | peerRows (groove-runtime + peer-mesh-store)
  ‚Üí UI ($derived)
```

Mesh snapshots go **only** via `avenos:runtime`. Do not add duplicate webview events for mesh payloads.

## Layer ownership

| Owner | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| `peeroxide` / `tauri-plugin-peer` | DHT, topics, Noise links, pairing codes, allowlisted socket acceptance, connect-UI hooks |
| `peer_mesh_state.rs` | Assemble `PeerMeshStatusReply` ‚Äî no Jazz CRUD |
| Groove actor (`jazz/runtime.rs`) | Serialize mesh_refresh / mesh_reconcile / publish_mesh; serial `conn` access |
| `jazz/mod.rs` | Allowlist sync, `register_peer_sync_client`, catch-up primitives |
| Frontend `peer-mesh-store.ts` + `groove-runtime.ts` | Single ingress; subscribe `peers` table for rows ‚Äî **no polling** |

## Actor ops

- **`publish_mesh`** ‚Äî snapshot only (JSON-deduped); use for connect-substate deltas, coarse `peer:mesh-push`, end of reconcile.
- **`mesh_refresh_full`** ‚Äî allowlist + Groove registration + publish; use after hyperswarm-ready, invite-paired persist, explicit retry.

Plugin emits coarse signals only (`peer:hyperswarm-ready`, `peer:invite-paired`, `peer:mesh-push`, `peer:connect-ui-changed`). App listeners forward to the actor ‚Äî **no** mesh assembly inside the plugin.

## Anti-patterns

- Second channel for mesh (`peer:mesh-*` payloads duplicate `avenos:runtime`).
- `refresh_peer_mesh_primitives` on every connect-progress tick ‚Äî prefer `publish_mesh`.
- `peerList()` IPC where `peers` table subscribe is active ‚Äî use `peerRows` store.
- Frontend `setInterval` / duplicate `meshStatus` pulls after user actions.

